Process Management

Viewing Process
ps → Displays the running process for the terminal.
ps aux → Lists all process w/ CPU & memory usage.
top → Real-time dynamic view for running process.

Process Control
kill PID → Sends a signal to terminate a process no (PID)
kill name → Kills process by process name
killall name → Terminates all process with the given name.

Background & Foreground
command & → Runs a command in the background
jobs → Lists background jobs in the current shell.
fg jobID → Brings a background job to the foreground.
bg jobID → Resumes a stopped job in the background.

Process Priority
nice -n value command → Starts a process w/ a given priority.
renice value PID → Changes priority of a running process.

Process Information
pidof process → Displays PID of a running process.
pgrep process → Searches process IDs by name or pattern.
pstree → Shows in a parent-child tree format.

Signals & Monitoring
$watch command → Repeats a command at regular intervals.
$uptime → Shows sys running time & load average.
$time command → Measures execution time of a command.

Daemon & System Process
systemctl status service → Shows status of a sys service.
systemctl start/stop/restart → start/stop/restart/enable a sys service
